{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"091970b1-01ff-4798-9d1b-a379bd1718d7","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_POHCWnR1FIf9wXPimXgHnK","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7719fdd032eb4078b5fa1b52b1c935ec/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7719fdd032eb4078b5fa1b52b1c935ec/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"c4997d24-abf3-4984-b4ca-c29720a1069a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":367,"requestId":"1907:271D55:131CCDE:1577F48:6A066E96"},"id":"f42ab650-172b-4251-bbae-29e9d689e0e4","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:50.532Z","parentId":"646b13ec-79df-451f-9c36-f0403ae0e730"}
